    Introduction

    This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

    As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

    Base URL

    http://localhost:8000

    Authenticating requests

    Authenticate requests to this API's endpoints by sending an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {token}".

    All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

    You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API token.

    Activity Logs

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/activity_logs/search" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/activity_logs/search"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://localhost:8000/api/activity_logs/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Example response (401):

    Show headers 
    cache-control: no-cache, private
content-type: application/json
 
    
{
    "message": "Unauthenticated."
}
    Received response:
    Request failed with error:

    Request      

    GET api/activity_logs/search

    Auth

    Reset Password

    requires authentication

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/auth/reset-password" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --data "{
    \"username\": \"john@mail.com\",
    \"token\": \"123010100101\",
    \"password\": \"mypassword02\"
}"

    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/auth/reset-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

let body = {
    "username": "john@mail.com",
    "token": "123010100101",
    "password": "mypassword02"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://localhost:8000/api/auth/reset-password',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'username' => 'john@mail.com',
            'token' => '123010100101',
            'password' => 'mypassword02',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Example response (200):

    
{
    "message": "Password reset successful"
}

    Example response (401):

    
{
    "message": "Error resetting password"
}
    Received response:
    Request failed with error:

    Request      

    POST api/auth/reset-password

    Body Parameters

    username  string  

    User email.

    token  string  

    Password Reset Token.

    password  string  

    New User Password.

    Register new user/member

    requires authentication

    This endpoint allows to create new user account.

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/auth/register" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --data "{
    \"first_name\": \"John\",
    \"last_name\": \"Ansah\",
    \"email\": \"john.ansah@mail.com\",
    \"gender\": \"male\",
    \"dob\": \"1980-01-03\",
    \"mobile_number\": \"+2332440000001\",
    \"password\": \"mypassword01\"
}"

    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/auth/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

let body = {
    "first_name": "John",
    "last_name": "Ansah",
    "email": "john.ansah@mail.com",
    "gender": "male",
    "dob": "1980-01-03",
    "mobile_number": "+2332440000001",
    "password": "mypassword01"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://localhost:8000/api/auth/register',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'first_name' => 'John',
            'last_name' => 'Ansah',
            'email' => 'john.ansah@mail.com',
            'gender' => 'male',
            'dob' => '1980-01-03',
            'mobile_number' => '+2332440000001',
            'password' => 'mypassword01',

);
$body = $response->getBody();

    Request      

    GET api/banks/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/banks/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=itaque" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/banks/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "itaque",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
    $client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://localhost:8000/api/banks/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'itaque',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Request      

    GET api/banks/search

    Query Parameters

    limit  string optional  

    Total items to return e.g. ?limit=15.

    page  integer optional  

    Page of items to return e.g. ?page=1.

    sort  string optional  

    Sorting options e.g. ?sort=field1:asc,field2:asc OR ?sort=latest/oldest.

    count  integer optional  

    Count related models. Alternatively with_count e.g. ?count=relation1,relation2.

    contain  string optional  

    Contain data from related model e.g. ?contain=relation1,relation2.

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/banks?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/banks"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
};

    Query Parameters

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/contribution_receipt_settings/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=cumque" \

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/contribution_receipts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=eos" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/contribution_receipts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "eos",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5

    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    Request      

    GET api/countries/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/countries/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=eos" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/countries/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "eos",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',

        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    Request      

    GET api/currencies/search

    Query Parameters

    limit  string optional  

    Total items to return e.g. ?limit=15.

    page  integer optional  

    Page of items to return e.g. ?page=1.

    sort  string optional  

    Sorting options e.g. ?sort=field1:asc,field2:asc OR ?sort=latest/oldest.

    count  integer optional  

    Count related models. Alternatively with_count e.g. ?count=relation1,relation2.

    contain  string optional  

    Contain data from related model e.g. ?contain=relation1,relation2.

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/currencies?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/currencies"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/member_images/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=molestiae" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/member_images/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "molestiae",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

    'http://localhost:8000/api/member_images/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'molestiae',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/members?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/members"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
};

    requires authentication

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5

    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/member_relations/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=ut" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/member_relations/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "ut",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/notifications?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/notifications"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_file_imports/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=at" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

);

    "fieldName": "at",
};

    Import File

    requires authentication

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_file_imports" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --form "organisation_id=1" \
    --form "import_to_id=1755514.3871347" \
    --form "import_type=contributions" \
    --form "import_file=@C:\Users\icewa\AppData\Local\Temp\php2B2B.tmp"

    "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_file_imports"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",

};

body.append('import_to_id', '1755514.3871347');
body.append('import_type', 'contributions');
body.append('import_file', document.querySelector('input[name="import_file"]').files[0]);

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());

        ],
        'multipart' => [
            [
                'name' => 'organisation_id',
                'contents' => '1'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_to_id',
                'contents' => '1755514.3871347'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_type',
                'contents' => 'contributions'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_file',
                'contents' => fopen('C:\Users\icewa\AppData\Local\Temp\php2B2B.tmp', 'r')
            ],
        ],
    ]
);

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    GET api/organisation_groups/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_groups/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=et" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_groups/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "et",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10

    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    Sorting options e.g. ?sort=field1:asc,field2:asc OR ?sort=latest/oldest.

    count  integer optional  

    Count related models. Alternatively with_count e.g. ?count=relation1,relation2.

    contain  string optional  

    Contain data from related model e.g. ?contain=relation1,relation2.

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_invoices/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=optio" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_invoices/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "optio",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",

    "Accept": "application/json",

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    fieldName  string optional

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_members/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=modi" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_members/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "modi",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",

    Get All

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_roles?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \

    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    GET api/organisation_settings/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_settings/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=non" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/organisation_settings/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "non",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/organisations/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=quae" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/organisations/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "quae",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",

    GET api/permissions/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/permissions/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=ducimus" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/permissions/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "ducimus",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    GET api/sms_accounts/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/sms_accounts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=architecto" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/sms_accounts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "architecto",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/sms_credits/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=qui" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/sms_credits/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "qui",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",

    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/subscription_types/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=quo" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \

    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    GET api/system_settings/count

    Query Parameters

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

    Search Resources

    requires authentication

    Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

    Options for searching

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/system_settings/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=qui" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/system_settings/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "qui",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
    Example request:
    curl --request GET \

    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \

    GET api/transaction_types/search

    Query Parameters

    limit  string optional  

    Total items to return e.g. ?limit=15.

    page  integer optional

    sort  string optional  

    Sorting options e.g. ?sort=field1:asc,field2:asc OR ?sort=latest/oldest.

    count  integer optional  

    Count related models. Alternatively with_count e.g. ?count=relation1,relation2.

    fieldName  string optional  

    Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field

    Get All

    requires authentication

    Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

    Options for searching / filtering

    • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
    • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
    • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
    • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
    • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
    • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
    • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
